  "elapsed_s": 5.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And, and then she suddenly pushed her plate away and looked at father and said, I heard today that both Eva and Vera can go to England.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And there was a deathly silence.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And my father suddenly looked [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] very pale and drawn, and [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] he buried his face in his hands.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And then he sighed and said, all right.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Let them go.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] It was a very, very strange movement and-- moment.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And after that, I mean, I was filled with excitement and apprehension.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I didn't know anyone from our town who'd ever been to England.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "You know, we-- suddenly my sister and I assumed great importance.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And it seemed like a big, big adventure.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And yet, we were both going to different places, I to a family in Liverpool I knew nothing about and my parents knew nothing about, and my sister to a school in Dorset.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] We were going to be separated, the two of us.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "You know, many years later, when I discovered the man who saved our lives and organized the transports, many people held it against him that he divided siblings, sent them to different places.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And he said, so wisely and so rightly, if I'd waited for a family who was willing to take two refugee children for unlimited time, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] you probably wouldn't be here today, because there were very few who would take more than one child.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Just the same was his reason for accepting any family, whether Jewish or Christian, even those who, who gave the condition of acceptance conversion to Christianity, because he said, I was after saving lives, not souls.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And this he did, very capably.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
